# Head-Aligned 3D Interaction System

A project combining **Python (MediaPipe + OpenCV)** and **Unity** to track head movement and align it with a 3D object in real time.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
## Link game demo:
	https://github.com/Godnona/Vr_with_face_detech.git

## Link src code:
 - Python: use to detech face
	https://github.com/Godnona/FaceTracking.git
 - Unity: use to build environment
	https://github.com/Godnona/Face_tracking_evironment.git
----------------------------------------------------------------------

## üß∞ Tools & Libraries
** Python 3.9 **
- MediaPipe 0.10.14 ‚Äì face tracking  
- OpenCV ‚Äì webcam processing  
- Socket, threading ‚Äì data streaming  
- PyInstaller ‚Äì build to .exe  

** Unity 2022.3.62f2 **
- C# socket receiver (`HandleReceiver.cs`)  
- 3D visualization and player control  
----------------------------------------------------------------------

## ‚öôÔ∏è How It Works
1. Python detects face landmarks using MediaPipe.  
2. Extracted (x, y, z) coordinates are sent to Unity via TCP.  
3. Unity updates cube/player rotation and position in real time.  
4. Tracking remains stable within ~5m range.
----------------------------------------------------------------------

## ‚ú® Features
- Real-time 3D face tracking  
- Python‚ÄìUnity live data streaming  
- Portable `.exe` builds (no fixed paths)  
- Low-latency updates  
